{
  "doc_id": "36859",
  "text": "On confirmation of successful retinal reattachment and completion of silicone oil exchange, the operating surgeon was asked to clinically grade the level of PVR using the standardized classification system in current practice. [CITATION_1] Thereafter, the surgeon was asked to inject a 0.7-mg slow-release dexamethasone implant through the final open sclerotomy port before suturing.",
